<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Punishment" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Punishment,</orth> 1) penalty, chastisement, correction: <bibl n="shak. pp 32" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 32</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.208" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 208</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.3.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 3, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.28" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 31</bibl>&lt;*&gt;.  <bibl n="shak. ado 5.4.130" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.270" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 270</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.176" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.130" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 130</bibl> <cit><quote>(to give).</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 105</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.183" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.94" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.274" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 274</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 1, 39</bibl> <cit><quote>(on pain of p.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 1.4.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 4, 129</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.11" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.334" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 334</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.334" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 334</bibl><lb />2) affliction, suffering: <cit><quote>the pleasing p. that women bear,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 47</bibl></cit> (but cf. <bibl n="Genesis 3.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Genesis III, 16</bibl>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>